  "body": "### Description\n\nThis issue is about exposing an OpenShift route or an ingress rule to expose a gRPC service. It will allow accessing gRPC services from outside the Kubernetes cluster. \n\n### Implementation ideas\n\nWe can either reuse the \"expose\" attribute or introduce a specific gRPC attribute to expose the route. \r\nThat feature would need documentation:\r\n\r\n- if the service is using plain/text, we should document how the route must be configured to use edge TLS termination\r\n- if the service is using TLS, we should document how the route must by-pass TLS checks",
